        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Since Valais Blacknose sheep appeared at Diddly Squat Farm on <em>Clarkson&rsquo;s Farm</em>, one fluffy, black-faced breed has been quietly stealing scenes from Jeremy Clarkson, Kaleb, and even the show&rsquo;s photogenic countryside. If you have searched "what breed of sheep did Lisa buy on Clarkson&rsquo;s Farm," you are in good company. Interest in the breed has climbed with every episode.
        </p>

